</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[603,3592,3348,5907]" pageId="15" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis box="[733,986,5273,5368]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="90">Skull.</emphasis>
Of the same general shape as in 
<emphasis box="[2697,3362,5273,5368]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="90">
<taxonomicName box="[2697,3347,5273,5368]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="90" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="borneensis">Rh. borneensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but much larger, with considerably larger teeth, and therefore longer tooth-row; orbital constriction very narrow. The following measurements, in millimetres, will give a more precise idea of the 
<emphasis box="[633,1097,5697,5792]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="90">differences</emphasis>
